"We used to be able to live real life with real money. Now we are playing a game with Monopoly money. We have been prevented from living real life; we are caught in a game. This did not come about by our conscious agreement. What if we want to go back to living real life? We’d have to get out of the game. This is tricky because the powers-that-be are capable of controlling us through confiscating our finances by keeping us in the game. Why would they allow us to opt out of a game which they are sure to win and which we are destined to lose? There is no way to stop playing the game unless we consciously do what it takes in order to extricate ourselves from the game. It is simple but not easy, mostly because the banksters refuse to lose. Also, most of us don’t realize we have a choice because most have never considered that we agreed to play a game we can’t win. Would anyone consciously choose to play such a game?"
#Repost @tylerdoll
・・・
"But money buys you the things you need".......I get that. So this inflated, manipulated, interest bearing debt note controlled by parasitical middle men is really the ONLY means to the necessities in life? I'm already kind of sick just thinking about how angry some people will be when they see this, I bare the burden of truth, you bare the burden of how you react to it. We have to come to a common understanding of the reality of what this paper currency is, it's the limiter, it's the resistor, it's a trap. I'm not some hippie that just wants to eat dirt and live in a treehouse (although that'd be a dope pad), I am a human being in slavery. I am a defined enemy of the state born on a battle field. I am the spirit operating an ego inflated meat puppet. But MOST of all, most importantly, I am you.
